<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,310,716,740]" box="[189,310,716,742]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,716,742]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,762,1000]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicName box="[189,287,763,788]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[189,287,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Begonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[362,534,762,788]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Microtuberosa</emphasis>
sect. nov. is most closely related to 
<emphasis box="[990,1015,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">B.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="A.DC., 1861 (Müll.Berol.)" authorityName="A.DC., 1861 (Müll.Berol.)" box="[1091,1275,762,788]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Trachelocarpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1091,1275,762,788]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Trachelocarpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and three species of 
<emphasis box="[316,341,798,823]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">B.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="A.DC., 1859 (Klotzsch)" authorityName="A.DC., 1859 (Klotzsch)" box="[412,517,797,823]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Gaerdtia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[412,517,797,823]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Gaerdtia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both of these sections are endemic to eastern Brazil and differ markedly from sect. 
<emphasis box="[313,485,833,859]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Microtuberosa</emphasis>
sect. nov. in both their habit and Foral characteristics (see 
<tableCitation box="[1174,1260,833,859]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="4.[189,258,268,294]" captionTargetBox="[189,1397,382,1199]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Table 1. Comparison between Begonia sect. Microtuberosa Moonlight &amp; Tebbitt sect. nov. and closely related sections." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/ABDA662AFFDBFF96FF30FEBC8E2EFE99" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" tableUuid="ABDA662AFFDBFF96FF30FEBC8E2EFE99">Table 1</tableCitation>
). However, all three sections share their Flaments fused at least at the base and 
<emphasis box="[1008,1033,869,894]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">B.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[1105,1277,868,894]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Microtuberosa</emphasis>
sect. nov. further shares its androecium morphology with 
<emphasis box="[755,780,904,929]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">B.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[850,939,904,929]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Pereira</emphasis>
and its lack of bracteoles with 
<emphasis box="[1312,1337,904,929]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">B.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="A.DC., 1861 (Müll.Berol.)" authorityName="A.DC., 1861 (Müll.Berol.)" box="[189,373,938,964]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Trachelocarpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[189,373,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Trachelocarpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The majority of both Foral and vegetative characters are, however, markedly different among the three sections.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,1039,1136]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicName box="[189,287,1040,1065]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[189,287,1040,1065]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Begonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[356,528,1039,1065]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Microtuberosa</emphasis>
sect. nov. is readily identiFed as the only Neotropical section of 
<taxonomicName box="[1301,1399,1040,1065]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1301,1399,1040,1065]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Begonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with male Fowers with four or fewer stamens, and the combination of ovaries with two or three locules and entire placentas, and a tuberous habit.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
